The White House has issued a letter stating that the national emergency declared in Executive Order 13664 with respect to South Sudan will continue beyond April 3, 2016. The letter highlights the ongoing threat to the peace, security, and stability of South Sudan and the surrounding region, including violence, human rights abuses, recruitment of child soldiers, attacks on peacekeepers, and obstruction of humanitarian operations. The extension of the national emergency is deemed necessary to protect the national security and foreign policy interests of the United States. The letter is signed by President Barack Obama.